# Conventional Commits

When generating commit messages, follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification.

- Use an appropriate type prefix: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, or `revert`.
- Write a clear, specific description in the imperative mood.
- Keep the subject line concise; add a body only when extra context is needed.
- Use a scope when it helps identify the affected area.

```text
feat(catalog): add sectioned layout to client create slideover
fix(auth): handle expired refresh token on login
test(clients): cover client create validation schema
```

Avoid vague subjects such as `update files`, `fix bug`, or `changes`.
